Johannesburg - Thirteen people were injured when a minibus taxi crashed in Midrand, Johannesburg on Saturday morning, paramedics said. Netcare 911 responded just before 9.30am to reports of a crash on the Pretoria main road in Midrand, Netcare 911 spokesman Shawn Herbst said. "Reports from the scene indicate that the driver of a minibus taxi lost control, resulting in the vehicle crashing down an embankment." A total of 13 people were injured in the crash, and once treated were transported by various ambulance services to hospital for further assessment, he said. African News Agency (ANA)